newsitem.title: CHINA: Shanghai soybean futures down on long liquidation.
newsitem.headline: Shanghai soybean futures down on long liquidation.

text.p: Shanghai soybean futures ended down on Wednesday on continued long liquidation, traders said.
The key March 1997 contract ended at 3,108 yuan per tonne, losing 32 yuan. It opened at an intra-day high of 3,150 and hit a low of 3,106.
May fell 100 to 3,117, July 71 to 3,251, November 17 to 3,361, and January 1998 fell 42 to 3,355. September was unchanged at 3,350.
Traders said investors were eager to liquidate their long positions with the approach of the Chinese new year holiday.
